  "source_notes": "Sy Scholfield quotes from \"Autobigrafía: o La vida de un hombre que se realiza en la historia\" by Nazario Chávez Aliaga (Librería Editorial \"Minerva\" Miraflores, 1973), p. 26: \"Dicho sea en verdad, nací contra mi gusto y contra mis ganas de no querer nacer a las 6 de la tarde, hora de tribulación y hora de blasfemia, hora que da vergüenza nacer... hora murmuradora... hora inmoral. Nací pues, circunstancialmente, en el pueblecito del Huauco, como hubiera podido nacer en Moscú, Pekín, New York, París, Roma o Madrid.\"\\n\\nTranslation:  It can truly be said that I was born against my will and against my desire of not wanting to be born, at 6 pm, with tribulation and in an hour of blasphemy, an ashamed hour ... an immoral hour. I was born, incidentally, in the village of Huauco, as one would have been born in Moscow, Beijing, New York, Paris, Rome or Madrid.\\n\\nHe was born in the village of Huauco (now called Sucre), located in the Province of Celendin Cajamarca, Peru.\\n",
